WEBVTT

00:01.418 --> 00:04.629
♪♪

00:04.713 --> 00:07.132
♪ We are The Fungies ♪

00:07.215 --> 00:10.510
♪ Prehistoric fungi
in a mushroom to-o-wn ♪

00:10.593 --> 00:11.928
♪ Outside, we look different ♪

00:12.011 --> 00:13.555
♪ Inside, we're the same ♪
Yeah!

00:13.638 --> 00:16.057
♪ Everyone's a Fungie
in their own way ♪

00:16.141 --> 00:18.393
♪ Come join The Fungies ♪

00:18.476 --> 00:21.730
♪ Explore a brand-new world
made just for yo-o-u ♪

00:21.813 --> 00:23.398
♪ If you're inclusive,
inquisitive ♪

00:23.481 --> 00:24.983
♪ Respectful, and kind ♪

00:25.066 --> 00:28.737
♪ You can be a Fungie, too ♪

00:28.820 --> 00:35.076
♪♪

00:35.160 --> 00:37.662
Jason:
<i>Gooooood morning, Fungietown!</i>

00:37.746 --> 00:39.789
<i>We've got reports</i>
<i>of scorching sandstorms</i>

00:39.873 --> 00:43.084
<i>raging in the badlands,</i>
<i>but here in Fungietown</i>

00:43.168 --> 00:46.254
<i>it's a balmy</i>
<i>30 degrees Mycelcius!</i>

00:46.337 --> 00:47.881
[ Sighs ]
Isn't this great, Pam?

00:47.964 --> 00:50.008
Why struggle out there
for survival

00:50.091 --> 00:51.509
in the middle
of a heat wave

00:51.593 --> 00:53.928
when you can stay here
and relax with us instead?

00:54.012 --> 00:57.432
It's strange, not having
to worry about survival.

00:57.515 --> 00:59.934
Jeepers,
it's so hot out here!

01:00.018 --> 01:03.271
Make sure that you stay
hydrated, my baby...

01:03.354 --> 01:06.274
and my lil' scaley baby.

01:06.357 --> 01:07.525
[ Slurping ]

01:07.609 --> 01:09.152
I like this kinda living!

01:09.235 --> 01:11.696
I don't have to walk
to a watering hole.

01:11.780 --> 01:12.989
Go on.

01:13.072 --> 01:15.867
I get endless snacks
from your bug barbecue.

01:15.950 --> 01:18.578
[ Insect buzzing, crackling ]

01:18.661 --> 01:19.954
Go on.

01:20.038 --> 01:21.790
And when the sun
harshes my eyes,

01:21.873 --> 01:26.127
I just use this
sweet hat you gave me!

01:26.211 --> 01:27.796
But the best part of all,

01:27.879 --> 01:31.132
I've always got my friend.
[ Sighs ]

01:31.216 --> 01:34.052
We're gonna have
a great summer, Pam.

01:34.135 --> 01:35.970
Jason:<i> Well, that's it</i>
<i>for today's jams.</i>

01:36.054 --> 01:38.223
<i>Go find some music</i>
<i>somewhere else,</i>

01:38.306 --> 01:39.891
<i>ya late night freaks.</i>

01:39.974 --> 01:41.643
[ Yawns ]

01:41.726 --> 01:44.979
I'd better get back
to the wild.

01:45.063 --> 01:46.606
Goodnight, Seth!

01:46.689 --> 01:47.816
[ Sighs ] Yeah.

01:47.899 --> 01:50.902
♪♪

01:50.985 --> 01:53.780
That's new.
Must be all the bugs.

01:53.863 --> 01:54.948
Worth it!

01:55.031 --> 01:57.158
Now, which way was nature?

01:57.242 --> 02:00.495
♪♪

02:00.578 --> 02:02.497
Oh hey, dinosaur!

02:02.580 --> 02:04.833
Nice dino hat!

02:04.916 --> 02:06.417
Yeah, it is nice!

02:06.501 --> 02:07.836
I think so too,

02:07.919 --> 02:09.546
so give it to me!

02:11.297 --> 02:13.007
You can't push me around.

02:13.091 --> 02:14.342
[ Inhales sharply ]

02:14.425 --> 02:16.427
[ Roars ]

02:16.511 --> 02:17.846
[ Burps ]

02:17.929 --> 02:19.597
Excuse me.

02:19.681 --> 02:21.391
Here comes the pinchie!

02:21.474 --> 02:23.226
[ Crabs laughing,
claws snapping ]

02:23.309 --> 02:25.103
Oh! Ow! Oh!

02:25.186 --> 02:27.522
Not so tough now,
are ya?

02:27.605 --> 02:30.525
♪♪

02:30.608 --> 02:32.944
Pam? Pam!

02:33.027 --> 02:35.655
I saw a cloud that looks
just like you...

02:35.738 --> 02:36.656
[ Gasps ]

02:36.739 --> 02:39.075
Pam?!
What happened?!

02:39.158 --> 02:40.118
They pinched me!

02:40.201 --> 02:42.662
And then
they pinched my hat.

02:42.745 --> 02:44.330
Why I oughta...!

02:44.414 --> 02:45.665
Look at me Seth.

02:45.748 --> 02:49.043
I've gone all adorable
and soft!

02:49.127 --> 02:50.670
Real soft.

02:50.753 --> 02:52.881
It's all this
easy living.

02:52.964 --> 02:56.634
I need to get my edge back --
my survivalist edge.

02:56.718 --> 02:59.262
Well, I don't think
you should blame yourself,

02:59.345 --> 03:01.556
but that<i> does</i>
sound pretty cool!

03:01.639 --> 03:04.726
I'm going to travel
to the heart of the badlands,

03:04.809 --> 03:06.269
regain my edge...

03:06.352 --> 03:08.563
or die trying.

03:08.646 --> 03:10.189
Sounds awesome!

03:10.273 --> 03:13.067
I just gotta tell my mom.

03:13.151 --> 03:14.861
I'll wait.

03:14.944 --> 03:15.820
♪♪

03:15.904 --> 03:17.196
Seth: The badlands...

03:17.280 --> 03:21.826
the harshest environment
in the known world.

03:21.910 --> 03:24.245
Fungies avoid it,

03:24.329 --> 03:28.750
and only the toughest dinos
call it home.

03:28.833 --> 03:33.880
If there's one place that can
make us tough, it's here.

03:33.963 --> 03:36.507
[ Coughs ] 'Scuse me, got
something in my throat.

03:36.591 --> 03:37.759
Hey, kiddos!

03:37.842 --> 03:39.260
Before I forget,

03:39.344 --> 03:42.263
I made you some sandwiches
for your little excursion!

03:42.347 --> 03:44.599
Pfft, toughies
don't need sandwiches!

03:44.682 --> 03:48.686
Not even slate sandwiches
with the crust cut off?

03:48.770 --> 03:51.773
Uhh, actually, yeah,
I think they eat those, yeah.

03:51.856 --> 03:53.816
Anyway...
I gotta blast!

03:53.900 --> 03:54.901
[ Laughs ]

03:54.984 --> 03:57.362
[ Motor revs ]

03:59.238 --> 04:01.741
Pam: Your mom rules.
Heh, yeah.

04:01.824 --> 04:04.953
Basically, the badlands
have three main dangers:

04:05.036 --> 04:08.831
the terrain, predators,
and the weather!

04:08.915 --> 04:10.667
So, all we have to do
is subject ourselves

04:10.750 --> 04:12.126
to each of these dangers,

04:12.210 --> 04:14.462
and then you'll
get back your edge!

04:14.545 --> 04:15.463
[ Gasps ]

04:15.546 --> 04:17.715
Rockfall Canyon.

04:17.799 --> 04:19.801
Let's go get tough!

04:21.552 --> 04:22.637
Seth!

04:22.720 --> 04:25.390
Oof. Just gotta
push through, y'know?

04:25.473 --> 04:26.432
Aah!

04:26.516 --> 04:29.560
Aah! Wha!
[ Breathing heavily ]

04:29.644 --> 04:30.979
Seth! Look out!

04:31.062 --> 04:32.814
[ Both grunting ]

04:32.897 --> 04:34.274
Ugh!

04:34.357 --> 04:36.734
Fall back!
Retreat!

04:36.818 --> 04:38.277
♪♪

04:38.361 --> 04:40.405
Whew.
That was close!

04:42.031 --> 04:43.241
[ Both scream ]

04:43.324 --> 04:45.743
Outta the way, softies!

04:45.827 --> 04:47.453
Aah!

04:47.537 --> 04:49.539
♪♪

04:49.622 --> 04:50.581
Ha!

04:50.665 --> 04:53.501
Don't you babies know?

04:53.584 --> 04:55.837
Life's gonna knock
the snot outta you,

04:55.920 --> 04:59.340
so you just gotta
knock it right back.

04:59.424 --> 05:01.134
Who was that?

05:03.094 --> 05:04.512
I want to be her.

05:04.595 --> 05:05.888
Me too.

05:05.972 --> 05:08.850
Y'know, her armor
gives me an idea.

05:10.768 --> 05:13.479
Just a couple
rock sandwiches...

05:13.563 --> 05:15.523
some glue...

05:15.606 --> 05:16.524
and...

05:16.607 --> 05:19.068
[ Grunts ]

05:19.152 --> 05:21.696
Now I've got
toughie armor too!

05:21.779 --> 05:22.780
My turn!

05:22.864 --> 05:24.949
[ Hisses ]

05:26.200 --> 05:29.037
[ Breathing heavily ]
Hey! Tough lady!

05:29.120 --> 05:30.955
Hold up a second!

05:31.039 --> 05:32.206
I'm Seth!

05:32.290 --> 05:33.583
I am Pam!

05:33.666 --> 05:36.461
Name's Scrandice, but I'm not
looking for friends.

05:36.544 --> 05:38.713
My only friend
is called...

05:38.796 --> 05:40.048
not dying.

05:40.131 --> 05:42.133
So edgy.

05:42.216 --> 05:44.052
Both: Scrandice, look out!

05:44.135 --> 05:46.721
♪♪

05:46.804 --> 05:48.097
Oh, dang!

05:48.181 --> 05:49.640
Are you okay?

05:49.724 --> 05:51.726
First rule of survival --

05:51.809 --> 05:54.604
never look back.

05:54.687 --> 05:56.189
Hoho, cool!

05:56.272 --> 05:58.024
What's
your metabolism like?

05:58.107 --> 05:59.484
Can you sweat
through your shell?

05:59.567 --> 06:00.777
Is your armor made up
of thousands

06:00.860 --> 06:02.904
of microscopic
compressed hairs or what?

06:02.987 --> 06:04.822
Oh, and how did your face
get like that?

06:04.906 --> 06:06.699
Seth: Pam! Rude.

06:06.783 --> 06:08.785
Second rule of survival --

06:08.868 --> 06:10.078
never smile.

06:10.161 --> 06:11.788
I guess I could try.

06:11.871 --> 06:16.084
♪♪

06:16.167 --> 06:18.795
[ Both growling ]

06:18.878 --> 06:20.129
Lesson's over!

06:20.213 --> 06:21.923
Huh?
Ah! Wait!

06:22.006 --> 06:23.966
We got so much more
to cover!

06:24.050 --> 06:25.468
Mmm.

06:25.551 --> 06:27.345
[ Insects buzzing ]

06:27.428 --> 06:29.222
Table scraps.

06:29.305 --> 06:30.932
Anything else
we should know?

06:31.015 --> 06:32.975
Here's your last lesson.

06:33.059 --> 06:34.435
Whoa!
Aah!

06:34.519 --> 06:36.104
♪♪

06:36.187 --> 06:37.855
Rule number 3 --

06:37.939 --> 06:40.817
don't trust anybody!

06:40.900 --> 06:43.111
Bold teaching strategy.

06:43.194 --> 06:44.445
What makes you say that?

06:44.529 --> 06:45.780
Rather than lecture us,

06:45.863 --> 06:47.824
I'm assuming Scrandice
pushed us into this canyon

06:47.907 --> 06:49.700
for a more kinesthetic
learning experi--

06:49.784 --> 06:51.077
[ Roaring ]
[ Both scream ]

06:51.160 --> 06:54.831
♪♪

06:54.914 --> 06:56.290
Ah!
[ Chuckles ]

06:56.374 --> 06:58.793
[ Both screaming ]

06:58.876 --> 07:02.505
[ Both giggling ]

07:02.588 --> 07:04.298
It's working!

07:04.382 --> 07:06.592
We're surviving!

07:06.676 --> 07:09.011
You're on your own,
now!

07:09.095 --> 07:11.556
Don't trust anyone,
right, Pam?

07:11.639 --> 07:12.723
Wha!

07:12.807 --> 07:15.268
Aah!

07:15.351 --> 07:17.311
[ Chuckles ]

07:17.395 --> 07:19.522
What did I tell ya
about smiling?

07:19.605 --> 07:21.816
Time out!
Got any legs I can borrow?

07:21.899 --> 07:23.985
[ Growling ]

07:24.068 --> 07:26.237
[ Roars ]

07:26.320 --> 07:30.324
[ Wind howling ]

07:30.408 --> 07:32.243
Yeah, you'd better run!

07:32.326 --> 07:34.078
'Cause I'm a real-deal
toughie now!

07:34.162 --> 07:36.289
They weren't running
from you.

07:36.372 --> 07:38.332
They were running
from that!

07:38.416 --> 07:41.002
♪♪

07:41.085 --> 07:43.337
That's a lotta sand.

07:43.421 --> 07:44.589
Outta my way.

07:44.672 --> 07:47.508
We gotta follow Scrandice
to high ground!

07:47.592 --> 07:49.135
Oof!
Later, chump!

07:49.218 --> 07:50.761
Here we go.

07:50.845 --> 07:53.973
Don't worry about me, Pam!

07:54.056 --> 07:55.141
I got this.

07:55.224 --> 07:57.101
No help at all!

07:57.185 --> 07:58.686
I'm coming up!

07:58.769 --> 08:00.980
Ha! Made it!

08:01.063 --> 08:02.356
Aah!

08:02.440 --> 08:03.357
Seth?

08:03.441 --> 08:05.067
[ Grunting ]

08:05.151 --> 08:06.694
I can't see!

08:06.777 --> 08:08.905
You know the rules.

08:08.988 --> 08:10.573
Never look back.

08:10.656 --> 08:12.950
Don't worry, I'm fine!

08:13.034 --> 08:14.160
Aah!

08:14.243 --> 08:15.828
A-a-ah!

08:15.912 --> 08:17.663
Aah!

08:17.747 --> 08:18.831
Seth?

08:18.915 --> 08:20.166
Oof!

08:20.249 --> 08:22.960
You know, when life
knocks the snot out of ya,

08:23.044 --> 08:25.463
you just gotta
knock it right back!

08:25.546 --> 08:26.505
[ Grunting ]

08:26.589 --> 08:28.883
[ Wind howling ]

08:28.966 --> 08:30.885
As long as I don't smile,

08:30.968 --> 08:33.471
I'll be okay!

08:33.554 --> 08:36.724
Don't smile!

08:36.807 --> 08:38.059
I'm proud of you.

08:38.142 --> 08:41.062
You let your own friend
bite the dust.

08:41.145 --> 08:45.566
That means more room
in the world for survivors.

08:45.650 --> 08:46.776
Survivors.

08:46.859 --> 08:48.277
Pam:
<i>But the best part of all...</i>

08:48.361 --> 08:50.655
<i>I've always got my friend!</i>

08:50.738 --> 08:52.490
I guess
I am a survivor.

08:52.573 --> 08:54.784
But I don't wanna survive
alone!

08:54.867 --> 08:57.078
♪♪

08:57.161 --> 08:59.330
Nice meeting you!

08:59.413 --> 09:02.083
Nobody help me!
I got this!

09:02.166 --> 09:05.002
I'm self-sufficient!

09:06.420 --> 09:08.381
Pam?!
Forget toughness!

09:08.464 --> 09:12.760
Why bother surviving if I can't
live with those I love!

09:12.843 --> 09:15.388
♪♪

09:16.681 --> 09:17.974
[ Insects chirping ]

09:18.057 --> 09:19.433
[ Both gasp ]

09:19.517 --> 09:21.269
We're alive?

09:21.352 --> 09:23.396
♪ We are alive ♪

09:23.479 --> 09:25.106
♪ We are alive ♪

09:25.189 --> 09:26.816
Yeah, but for how long?!

09:26.899 --> 09:29.610
How long until
the world finishes you off?

09:29.694 --> 09:32.488
While I live forever!

09:32.572 --> 09:34.282
The immortal Scrand--

09:34.365 --> 09:36.242
Aah!

09:36.325 --> 09:37.368
Ack!

09:39.578 --> 09:42.957
Ah, you think you got me,
death?!

09:43.040 --> 09:45.126
Just wait until
I get out of here --

09:46.711 --> 09:49.046
You...saved me?

09:49.130 --> 09:51.757
Like a couple 'a chumps.

09:51.841 --> 09:55.177
How do you know
that I won't steal your food

09:55.261 --> 09:57.305
or make you into a coat?

09:57.388 --> 09:59.265
We don't!
We'd just rather live

09:59.348 --> 10:01.100
in a world
where we help each other out.

10:01.183 --> 10:02.226
[ Ding! ]

10:04.061 --> 10:05.271
Least I can do is

10:05.354 --> 10:08.649
make sure you get home
not dead.

10:08.733 --> 10:14.905
♪♪

10:14.989 --> 10:17.575
Nice house, Nancy --

10:17.658 --> 10:21.203
even if it could use some,
ah, fortifying?

10:21.287 --> 10:23.456
I like you, Scrandice.

10:23.539 --> 10:26.334
You're no-nonsense,
and I like that!

10:26.417 --> 10:29.503
Maybe we should go for
a hog ride together sometime!

10:29.587 --> 10:30.838
[ Lively conversation
in distance ]

10:30.921 --> 10:33.007
Oh, no.
Not again.

10:33.090 --> 10:35.843
Yeah, I've been in touch with
a couple of modeling agencies.

10:35.926 --> 10:37.678
They want me to act,
too!

10:37.762 --> 10:39.221
Need a hand?

10:39.305 --> 10:41.015
So, anyway...

10:41.098 --> 10:42.183
Hey, where ya...?

10:42.266 --> 10:43.684
Huh?

10:43.768 --> 10:44.894
Oh, you again.

10:44.977 --> 10:48.230
[ Growling ]

10:48.314 --> 10:49.857
Uhhh...
[ Chuckles nervously ]

10:49.940 --> 10:51.067
Thanks, Scrandice.

10:51.150 --> 10:52.985
You're a real friend.

10:53.069 --> 10:54.862
Ahh...I am?

10:54.945 --> 10:58.783
♪♪

10:58.866 --> 11:00.868
Both: Wow!

11:00.951 --> 11:03.996
How exfoliating!

11:04.080 --> 11:05.373
[ Chuckles ]

11:05.456 --> 11:11.754
♪♪

11:11.837 --> 11:18.094
♪♪

11:18.177 --> 11:19.637
So edgy.
